{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.39",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 39,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 39",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 39 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:1",
      "text": "“Do you know when the mountain goats bring forth? Do you observe the calving of the hinds?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:2",
      "text": "Can you number the months that they fulfil, and do you know the time when they bring forth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:3",
      "text": "when they crouch, bring forth their offspring, and are delivered of their young?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:4",
      "text": "Their young ones become strong, they grow up in the open; they go forth, and do not return to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:5",
      "text": "“Who has let the wild ass go free? Who has loosed the bonds of the swift ass,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:6",
      "text": "to whom I have given the steppe for his home, and the salt land for his dwelling place?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:7",
      "text": "He scorns the tumult of the city; he hears not the shouts of the driver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:8",
      "text": "He ranges the mountains as his pasture, and he searches after every green thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:9",
      "text": "“Is the wild ox willing to serve you? Will he spend the night at your crib?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:10",
      "text": "Can you bind him in the furrow with ropes, or will he harrow the valleys after you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:11",
      "text": "Will you depend on him because his strength is great, and will you leave to him your labor?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:12",
      "text": "Do you have faith in him that he will return, and bring your grain to your threshing floor?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:13",
      "text": "“The wings of the ostrich wave proudly; but are they the pinions and plumage of love?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:14",
      "text": "For she leaves her eggs to the earth, and lets them be warmed on the ground,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:15",
      "text": "forgetting that a foot may crush them, and that the wild beast may trample them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:16",
      "text": "She deals cruelly with her young, as if they were not hers; though her labor be in vain, yet she has no fear;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:17",
      "text": "because God has made her forget wisdom, and given her no share in understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:18",
      "text": "When she rouses herself to flee, she laughs at the horse and his rider.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:19",
      "text": "“Do you give the horse his might? Do you clothe his neck with strength?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:20",
      "text": "Do you make him leap like the locust? His majestic snorting is terrible.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:21",
      "text": "He paws in the valley, and exults in his strength; he goes out to meet the weapons.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:22",
      "text": "He laughs at fear, and is not dismayed; he does not turn back from the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:23",
      "text": "Upon him rattle the quiver, the flashing spear and the javelin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:24",
      "text": "With fierceness and rage he swallows the ground; he cannot stand still at the sound of the trumpet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:25",
      "text": "When the trumpet sounds, he says ‘Aha!’ He smells the battle from afar, the thunder of the captains, and the shouting.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:26",
      "text": "“Is it by your wisdom that the hawk soars, and spreads his wings toward the south?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:27",
      "text": "Is it at your command that the eagle mounts up and makes his nest on high?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:28",
      "text": "On the rock he dwells and makes his home in the fastness of the rocky crag.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:29",
      "text": "Thence he spies out the prey; his eyes behold it afar off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.39.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:30",
      "text": "His young ones suck up blood; and where the slain are, there is he.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
